			"notice": "Stores encrypted medical record IPFS hashes on-chain and enforces         patient-controlled, time-limited consent before allowing access. CHANGES FROM v1:  - Interface updated to use hasValidConsent() — now checks expiry too  - Record versioning: each patient has a version counter; updates append    a new record rather than overwrite (immutable audit trail)  - RecordAccessed event now includes the accessor's role string  - getRecordsByPatient() added for frontend pagination  - nonReentrant guard on all write functions  - viewMedicalRecord split: returns hash + emits access log",
